This paper deals with graphical models and conditional independence, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). It also involves the use of partial correlations, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the structure of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs), which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
